Pakistan is a country located in South Asia.
The capital city of Pakistan is Islamabad,
while Karachi is its largest city and main economic hub.
Pakistan gained independence in 1947.
The official language is Urdu, and English is also widely used.
The currency of Pakistan is the Pakistani Rupee.
The country has diverse geography, including mountains, deserts, and rivers.
The Indus River is the longest river in Pakistan.
Pakistan is the fifth most populous country in the world.
Cricket is the most popular sport in the country.